Package com.here.android.mpa.urbanmobility

The package urbanmobility provides classes, callbacks, and enumerations that can be used to enable functionality related to public transit such as search for nearby transit stations and requests for departure boards.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ResponseListener<T>
    Represents a listener to provide information about RequestManager events concerting request execution.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDeparture<T extends AbstractDepartureImpl>
    Base class for Departure and AlternativeDeparture.
    AbstractRequest<T>
    Represents an abstract request and provides access to common request parameters.
    Address
    Represents information about an address: coordinates, street name, postal code etc.
    AlternativeDeparture
    Represents information about an alternative departure.
    Departure
    Represents information about a departure.
    DepartureBoard
    Represents departure information for a public transport at a given stop/station.
    DepartureBoardRequest
    Represents a request to retrieve a station next departures board.
    DepartureFrequency
    Represents information about departure frequencies.
    Line
    Represents a public transport line.
    LineCategory
    Represents the category information for the public transport line.
    LineStyle
    Represents the styling guideline information for the public transport line.
    Link
    Represents a link which can be associated with operator, transit alert or a ticket.
    Operator
    Represents a public transport operator.
    RealTimeInfo
    Represents real-time information of a departure or arrival.
    RequestManager
    Represents a manager responsible for executing request to UrbanMobility/Transit API, with a ResponseListener to trigger appropriate callback methods upon completion.
    Station
    Represents information about a Station.
    StationSearchRequest
    Represents a request to search stations within certain radius by name, geo-coordinates or IDs.
    StationSearchResult
    Station Search result which contains a List of found Stations and, when requested, a Collection of all unique Lines that run through those stations.
